docs.lead_paragraph: There are any number of ways to be bitten by an alligator, but some are more reliable than others, a paper by an epidemiologist in North Carolina reports. Topping the list, few may be surprised to learn, is trying to pick up or catch an alligator. Swimming in an area thick with the reptiles comes in at No. 2. Retrieving lost golf balls is also high on the list.

headline.main: Alligator Attacks Increasing (Don't Pick One Up)
